09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/3938e76a-54d4-4d00-a2f8-120dd494d8db" class="r-1b5b47t" loading="eager"/></picture><div data-rid="9690fc78-b8e4-41db-9038-6d1a926e714f" class="r-1pa2bm7"><div data-rid="cc37a4a0-5b9e-4621-a3d6-aeaf67b80618" class="r-1lji1x5"><div data-rid="bf87ac2e-9a0a-4be5-96b9-4b61e1b4a334" class="r-f8s6os alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">Edna Lilienstein</span></div></div><div data-rid="e89ee646-d5a5-4fcd-992c-785d375a41f3" class="r-1wkef81 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Health & Wellness Editor · 8 min read · March 2026</p></span></div></div></div><picture data-rid="a3ed1428-e8f2-4961-bf9e-5fe49756f226" class="r-uvde16"><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/657aa317-3d2d-422a-9f80-099a17152470?width=706" media="(max-width: 640px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/657aa317-3d2d-422a-9f80-099a17152470?width=706" media="(min-width: 641px) and (max-width: 1024px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/657aa317-3d2d-422a-9f80-099a17152470?width=706" media="(min-width: 1025px) and (max-width: 2400px)"/><img src="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/657aa317-3d2d-422a-9f80-099a17152470" alt="A middle-aged man with glasses and a goatee stands indoors in front of two windows with plaid curtains." class="r-1q0xrzz" loading="eager"/></picture><div data-rid="42bfbf26-f24c-41d8-ac70-489da85a4bcf" class="r-aqmoxs"><div data-rid="645f44d2-0320-4f17-856c-c68bb61bc79d" class="r-11zcjb3 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>Dave, 59, sharing his story for the first time.</p></span></div></div><div data-rid="b6fed35d-94b9-4c85-b736-f2732460917c" class="r-1si722o"><div data-rid="f9a4f94b-6b9c-44bb-8f34-3136b7cd631b" class="r-197wqda alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">Dave was born with something most<br>people never have to think about.</span></div></div><div data-rid="bcf64340-1f6f-4c0d-bb29-64b91a2a3cc7" class="r-11jx8io"><div data-rid="0a7f512f-73eb-4bcf-adda-7ed699da60e6" class="r-1whswes alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">When he was an infant, doctors found a<br>spot on his lung. Back then, nobody quite<br>understood what it was.</span></div></div><div data-rid="f9e0a571-4926-4baf-928c-745c06ab0c50" class="r-c6ozom"><div data-rid="f2ec6a7a-a3c1-4498-b726-cbe97dad5f98" class="r-1oleh7l alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">So they removed it.</span></div></div><div data-rid="949986f6-d960-4a17-8b65-8aa43ab36501" class="r-1odnaim"><div data-rid="9f0ba90f-633a-43ea-8e6d-f0b80db510c0" class="r-t2ame1 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">They took out a fifth of his lung.</span></div></div><div data-rid="2beec1c9-3e88-4561-81e6-b8c7ad5b8f19" class="r-12482rh"><div data-rid="582b96f4-62b1-4208-b90b-008f0a95faff" class="r-5gs8aa alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">He grew up with a scar that ran from his<br>chest all the way around his back.</span></div></div><div data-rid="05cbdba0-e6d5-4931-9f88-5727e41fbf6e" class="r-i6cgaw"><div data-rid="8c2d0f91-a00f-45d9-8fd1-eee5bba7f9d6" class="r-137yqa3 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">He also has a condition called pectus<br>excavatum — a visible indentation in his<br>chest. When he took his shirt off as a kid,<br>people would stare.</span></div></div><div data-rid="2c72f7fe-e229-487b-ae97-8d7a32510afa" class="r-1m046o5"><div data-rid="201db1f1-4ef0-4872-9e2d-e91300979649" class="r-tdgzrx"><div data-rid="ab931659-1630-497d-9d96-05fb7504bd76" class="r-118kmy alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">“People would say, ‘Can you breathe okay?’ And I’d say, ‘I have no idea. Do you breathe okay?’”</span></div></div><div data-rid="661084c1-29ee-458e-b6fd-aeb78745d058" class="r-19la0ls"><div data-rid="46b1de70-97b3-4476-9c11-f63b62c7c052" class="r-5nlbww alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">— Dave, age 59</span></div></div></div><div data-rid="ba2fdd50-1b2c-4539-a3c2-766b0ffeb894" class="r-1hgf5id"><div data-rid="4ac01786-1abf-4f4b-8e5a-f104ebbb18eb" class="r-1kek0ap alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">His parents told him it was cosmetic. Not a<br>big deal.</span></div></div><div data-rid="c7f56400-1b0e-414e-b77d-7331bb421d18" class="r-1rcw0lo"><div data-rid="0db4e7c8-9fa4-497a-ac9b-93655aba6f83" class="r-lupgl3 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">So Dave played ice hockey. He did sports.<br>He did everything the other kids did.</span></div></div><div data-rid="21f234b2-5853-4ecb-903b-53c14b123384" class="r-1nxqn1v"><div data-rid="617b9686-aee7-45c3-9e3c-6c4ee400ed9b" class="r-1yeouwi alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">But there were signs he didn’t recognize<br>at the time.</span></div></div><div data-rid="df3b3d5c-0d41-4f51-b6dd-238e1e2505d4" class="r-1ya6hmj"><div data-rid="98643324-c43e-4514-a2ca-4a9a3d427690" class="r-l2o8ms alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">He lived in a third-floor apartment.<br>Running up the stairs as a ten-year-old,<br>he’d stop at the second landing to catch his<br>breath.</span></div></div><div data-rid="6f702f05-b38e-4a80-9182-df91f463c39a" class="r-c5pe1d"><div data-rid="0bfbc58a-52f4-4f83-899d-63f9f7a75c76" class="r-1u0wioh alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">He played goalie in hockey — because<br>skating up and down the ice left him<br>winded.</span></div></div><div data-rid="3182397a-5982-4cfd-9794-06edcfc7a788" class="r-6qcvu9"><div data-rid="1307092c-131f-4abb-8dbe-ebdb2efb8f5b" class="r-1x6r1s0 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">His siblings loved swimming at the YMCA.<br>Dave didn’t — he’d get tired too fast.</span></div></div><div data-rid="a98c1b8a-fb53-4ebf-a4a3-22108d0ce464" class="r-1qidw0l"><div data-rid="47818bc9-3e13-4aca-b9e1-67aa102fd7e9" class="r-uw3w1c alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">“All those factors raised red flags later,”<br>Dave says. “But I didn’t really think about it<br>until I got older.”</span></div></div><div data-rid="189d208b-9ad6-4043-9da3-18e74eeb239d" class="r-mcsp6w"></div><div data-rid="468d0e01-02ab-4489-8a5a-377d938e3a33" class="r-fb565g"><div data-rid="14dd52a7-3552-4fc8-8ea3-a823c152b6f3" class="r-z1pcqy alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">Then Everything Changed<br>Overnight</span></div></div><div data-rid="4333cc50-4961-442b-8d0d-095ce613459c" class="r-1tcen56"><div data-rid="88b5e85f-438c-490f-a586-4bec1d320127" class="r-j3e90w alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">A few years ago, Dave got hit hard with a<br>respiratory illness.</span></div></div><div data-rid="f45e0607-07a2-44ae-a9dd-68f960bf0b5e" class="r-yj9kpe"><div data-rid="5f7e0ed8-ae1d-4a18-8bbd-495c80cd3688" class="r-qcmjcj alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">He didn’t think of himself as someone at<br>risk. He’d never thought of his breathing as<br>a real problem.</span></div></div><div data-rid="eb99fe16-0dfb-4678-9b01-52a6d68569f4" class="r-1m0mlxa"><div data-rid="22708ab5-78b6-40d0-af08-f52282a5e772" class="r-733j8u alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">But his body told a different story.</span></div></div><div data-rid="283fda5d-d9e1-4f33-b33f-56836477df3e" class="r-1wyhmu9"><div data-rid="1e673168-c688-4370-8a55-964abc076405" class="r-7o81bo alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">He was hospitalized for six days. Then he<br>got sick again and spent another five days<br>in the hospital.</span></div></div><div data-rid="ddd7fed4-2a5b-4605-811f-02eb3d1c64ae" class="r-1dkpxef"><div data-rid="368eead5-6af1-4198-8096-8cbfb767a44c" class="r-f3ehvg alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">When he finally came home, things were<br>different.</span></div></div><div data-rid="f4565d59-288d-4d08-b24a-9c06c5118c75" class="r-158lcjz"><div data-rid="98b1ea4c-2435-4935-8d13-88dfbfa481a5" class="r-brjrhe alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">He was on oxygen.</span></div></div><picture data-rid="edf57dfe-aea7-42bf-836a-62a49d2499ee" class="r-n3drns"><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/57a04f3b-a2b6-43fd-9fd3-a5c68e49924c?width=706" media="(max-width: 640px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/57a04f3b-a2b6-43fd-9fd3-a5c68e49924c?width=706" media="(min-width: 641px) and (max-width: 1024px)"/><source srcSet="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/57a04f3b-a2b6-43fd-9fd3-a5c68e49924c?width=706" media="(min-width: 1025px) and (max-width: 2400px)"/><img src="https://assets.replocdn.com/projects/6bf67db6-09d6-4705-bab2-a1af9067f5a3/57a04f3b-a2b6-43fd-9fd3-a5c68e49924c" alt="A person in a hospital gown with medical tubing sits on a bed in a dimly lit room." class="r-2ty3v4" loading="eager"/></picture><div data-rid="a22e80bd-4fdd-42ac-918c-2b474f5841d6" class="r-1al2ko7"><div data-rid="9f00f2e5-9fa1-40b5-83f7-35ee24e06b51" class="r-2msyam alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">His doctor sat him down. They went<br>through years of history — the childhood<br>surgery, the stairs, the swimming, the<br>hockey.</span></div></div><div data-rid="de93e03a-d11d-4d7c-be6c-5e5b0412206d" class="r-ik2qpb"><div data-rid="254c49f0-387c-4134-b56a-05d5cd0576cb" class="r-ukvbvw alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">All those little moments that never seemed<br>like a big deal suddenly painted a very clear<br>picture.</span></div></div><div data-rid="9b1bc919-43b0-40bd-8929-9ef56c64c58d" class="r-1jetpzm"><div data-rid="1abdfd7c-989a-4276-8d0c-33312768ae33" class="r-19tjnty"><div data-rid="9ac7c0da-ceca-4482-9801-c867df462c2e" class="r-fhtd5c alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>“My doctor said, ‘Do you know what your diagnosis is?’ I said I had no idea. He said, ‘Because you have everything. That’s why you have no idea.’”</p></span></div></div><div data-rid="413df654-68cc-4b25-829a-3527ff4a8c90" class="r-k2oj57"><div data-rid="0a28fa72-f6f7-4065-b47d-bb2e04e58d10" class="r-7n5ua2 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p>— Dave</p></span></div></div></div><div data-rid="46c46662-2815-4575-8323-6052aa3a2743" class="r-1dkxqh2"><div data-rid="3ce7a552-0208-444c-852b-e3bd9a04cab3" class="r-zhzofa alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">By last July, his doctors told him his lungs<br>had been through too much.</span></div></div><div data-rid="8cdd4331-9dcc-4e0c-abd7-f12e226f8744" class="r-1u4v8h3"><div data-rid="85ac3a03-351a-4b44-ad53-20c587c07ef0" class="r-17ocwb alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">They weren’t sure they could help him<br>anymore.</span></div></div><div data-rid="4b96d54c-e405-48f5-8794-76fe60d43325" class="r-1o6u1b1"><div data-rid="beb4385f-a0f9-4ca3-b74e-13790508348f" class="r-efrohv alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">The options they were considering were<br>major — the kind of interventions that<br>come with serious risks, especially for<br>someone with Dave’s other health<br>challenges.</span></div></div><div data-rid="f7052455-43c4-47c9-bcb4-ecf6be3ae2ca" class="r-1s3l8ut"><div data-rid="d8f8a266-1af6-4ed5-9f4b-92514d8825a3" class="r-245wob alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">“I panicked,” Dave says. “I didn’t know<br>what to do.”</span></div></div><div data-rid="37675e5b-c387-4915-97ec-33fa24c77372" class="r-19r92ju"></div><div data-rid="10ae912d-2353-4203-a970-7611e4d778b5" class="r-z738rc"><div data-rid="d8ae53bb-b14d-47d5-9099-f7de2e93f6c6" class="r-qoqj79 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">“My Sister Is a Botanist. She<br>Handed Me a Bottle and Said,<br>‘Just Try It.’”</span></div></div><div data-rid="005bb1c2-31a7-4714-9608-1ad86cf73d7d" class="r-1cbrzth"><div data-rid="cf5a3e4e-b6ea-4910-8d48-f8b77c037104" class="r-lo62lb alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">Dave’s sister owns a plant store. She’s<br>spent her career studying botanical<br>remedies.</span></div></div><div data-rid="56b4d155-3fb6-4c84-9fab-31d673a86008" class="r-bg4pq"><div data-rid="1c46b7a6-44fd-4aa1-914b-30582dcf4abd" class="r-1kq1756 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">The kind of thing most people dismiss as<br>“folk medicine” — until they’re desperate<br>enough to try anything.</span></div></div><div data-rid="79cbdb55-a97a-4973-a4db-ef49fbb3ea67" class="r-1frp5xo"><div data-rid="4d9eb454-aad4-43de-a33d-ee7fa001877d" class="r-oin3oq alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">She told Dave about mullein.</span></div></div><div data-rid="0493176c-dca6-481c-a3aa-09155580fec3" class="r-1bt6u19"><div data-rid="cec71ec6-d341-46be-a5e2-2dcb0e26514a" class="r-105w6xz alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p><span>Mullein (<em>Verbascum thapsus</em>) is a flowering plant that’s been used for respiratory wellness for over 2,000 years.</span></p></span></div></div><div data-rid="72a17504-8620-4bd9-8bb5-3ff94f8c6453" class="r-dyrsu0"><div data-rid="74bb431b-5e9d-417f-9bdb-7c4cf4ca3531" class="r-bzdvbn alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%"><p><span>Grandmothers in Appalachia, herbalists in<br>Europe, and traditional healers across Asia<br>have all independently relied on it, long<br>before anyone understood <em>why</em> it seemed<br>to help.</span></p></span></div></div><div data-rid="d568adf2-b961-4ba0-a8da-f1268e7bfe79" class="r-1n4mb87"><div data-rid="62d157ea-ce3e-4fed-a761-7ac94c863ddd" class="r-1kiw0oq alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">Dave’s sister gave him the information and<br>told him to run with it.</span></div></div><div data-rid="c4bbb2a0-97ce-4ff5-8400-d2fb5a507dc0" class="r-1iy4dgp"><div data-rid="7ea73f84-c23b-4b85-8d88-ab410d64bc86" class="r-hsnrf2 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">“I did some research,” Dave says. “And I<br>found </span></div><div data-rid="52a0b345-45f4-405a-aa7f-b589e333ae03" class="r-1w387ul"><a data-rid="7b40f3cb-52d9-469e-b10a-eafb9a72f47d" tabindex="0" role="link" class="r-mtlh04 alchemy-rte" target="_top" href="https://www.trybetterbrand.com/collections/tincture/products/betterlungs%C2%AE-mullein-chlorophyll?variant=50211235922219"><p>BetterLungs®</p></a></div><div data-rid="d69491d2-cec7-4451-9fc9-6bc500461264" class="r-vuwak4 alchemy-rte"><span style="width:100%">.